<p><hi rend="underline">Statement of Sales of</hi> Darwin’s Origin of Species<ref target="#foot.f1"/> | 1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> Feby <hi rend="underline">186</hi>8</p>
<p><hi rend="underline">by D. APPLETON &amp; CO. for account of</hi> Asa Gray</p>
                            <table rend="left">
                                <row>
                                    <cell rend="borderTop right"><hi rend="underline">On hand last account....</hi></cell>
                                    <cell rend="right borderSides borderTop">148</cell>
                                    <cell rend="borderTop right"><hi rend="underline">On hand this date....</hi></cell>
                                    <cell rend="right borderSides borderTop">350</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rend="right"><hi rend="underline">Printed since.... .... .</hi></cell>
                                    <cell rend="right borderSides">500</cell>
                                    <cell rend="right"><hi rend="underline">Given away.... ....</hi></cell>
                                    <cell rend="borderSides"/>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell/>
                                    <cell rend="borderSides"/>
                                    <cell rend="right"><hi rend="underline">Sold to date .... ....</hi></cell>
                                    <cell rend="right borderSides">298</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell/>
                                    <cell rend="right borderSides borderTop borderBottom">648</cell>
                                    <cell/>
                                    <cell rend="right borderSides borderTop borderBottom">648</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell cols="2"><hi rend="underline">Sold</hi> 298 <hi rend="underline">Copies.</hi> $2<hi rend="superscript">50</hi>
                                        <hi rend="underline">Rate</hi> 5%</cell>
                                    <cell/>
                                    <cell rend="right">$ 37.25</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>Jany 1/67 By Balance</cell>
                                    <cell cols="2"/>
                                    <cell rend="right">115.86</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell cols="3"/>
                                    <cell rend="right">$153.11</cell>
                                </row>
                            </table> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">This statement gives sales figures for the US edition of <hi rend="italic">Origin.</hi> Gray had negotiated the original terms of publication of the book with Appleton &amp; Co. (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 8, Appendix IV). Gray may have enclosed the statement in his <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5921.xml">letter of 24 February 1868</ref>, or his <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5928.xml">letter of 25 February [1868]</ref>.</note>
